🎤 Interview Question

You are given an employee DataFrame with the following columns:

emp_id, name, department, salary

Write PySpark code to perform the following tasks:

1. Display the name column as employee_name.


2. Display the salary column as employee_salary.


3. Display a new column named annual_salary (salary × 12).


4. Display only these three columns:

employee_name

employee_salary

annual_salary




> Do not modify the original DataFrame.




---

📊 Input Dataset

emp_id	name	department	salary

101	John	IT	60000
102	David	HR	45000
103	Alice	IT	70000
104	Bob	Finance	55000
105	Sam	HR	48000



---

✅ Expected Output

employee_name	employee_salary	annual_salary

John	60000	720000
David	45000	540000
Alice	70000	840000
Bob	55000	660000
Sam	48000	576000



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.functions import col

df.select(
    col("name").alias("employee_name"),
    col("salary").alias("employee_salary"),
    (col("salary") * 12).alias("annual_salary")
).show()


---

⭐ Alternative Solution

Using DataFrame column notation:

df.select(
    df.name.alias("employee_name"),
    df.salary.alias("employee_salary"),
    (df.salary * 12).alias("annual_salary")
).show()


